grep
	Glogal regular expression is used to find text inside a file
at default grep is case sensitive

-v	exclude the given word and print the lines

-n	gives line number that the word was found

-c	gives the count of the word repeated

-i	tells not to care about case sensitivity

-r	it allows to recursively check the files even through directories

ex
grep Port /etc/ssh/sshd_config  gives the line containing Port
grep -ri error /var/log
